  "edge_hypothesis": "Bollinger Band breakouts detect volatility expansion — when price breaks above BBU or below BBL, a compressed market is expanding directionally. This mechanism is fundamentally different from existing ACCEPTs which are transition-detection (Vortex, Ichimoku) or mean-reversion (KAMA). Adding Vortex directional dominance (VTXP vs VTXM comparison, not crossover) as a confirmation filter ensures we only enter breakouts that have genuine directional pressure behind them, not random wicks. The bollinger_breakout template has been blacklisted by the pipeline but was never tested with Vortex confirmation — a novel combination. Hypothesis: volatility expansion breakouts filtered by directional momentum produce a distinct edge profile in transitional and trending regimes.",
